"""Focused test: try HIGH wtq (tile median-ish) to avoid autofluorescence
outliers in the shallow tail of per-column tops.

Also test an adaptive-quantile: use wtq=0.50 when tile dynamic range is
large (autofluorescence dominant), wtq=0.10 when tile is tight.
"""
